HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 416
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Elijah Talley, 2025 Top
Ten Senior of Zion Christian Academy.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Elijah Talley is one such exceptional student, who was recently named a
Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Zion Christian Academy; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Talley has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Elijah Talley has earned an exemplary
grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Talley's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success; and
WHEREAS, Elijah Talley's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
his family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Talley's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of the members of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor Elijah Talley on being named a 2025 Zion
Christian Academy Top Ten Senior, salute his impressive academic achievement, and extend to
him our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
